<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="352" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1097,1269]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1097,1122]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Very small to large species with body size varying from about 1.0 to 5.0 mm, recognised by the following combination of characters: eyes separated in both sexes, bare; postpronotal lobe well differentiated; scutum usually distinctly longer than broad; mid leg raptorial, mid femur thickened and armed with rows of spinelike setae ventrally, mid tibia usually with more or less prominent apical spur; wing with veins A 
<number box="[1227,1235,1220,1234]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="1.0">1</number>
and CuA 
<number box="[1341,1349,1220,1234]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="2.0">2</number>
present (cell cup present).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
